# RaspberryPi GPIO Button Reboot
A button that if pressed and held for under 3 seconds,
initiates the reboot command, and if held for over 3 seconds,
initiates the halt command.

## Components
* x1 Tactile switch
* x1 1k om Resistor
* x1 10k om Resistor

## Setup Instructions
Assemble breadboard as per circut.png and breadboard.png

### RPi.GPIO script
btnReboot.py
Copy to /opt/gpio

### Debian load on boot script
gpio-btnreboot 
Copy to /etc/init.d

Finished

